  "mitigation_currently_implemented": "Deploy a pre-configured Snort IPS inline on the Internet egress path so it immediately inspects and blocks C2/exfil patterns and anomalous outbound tunnels (behavioral and signature detection) as a network-level prevention layer.",
  "comments": "I added a Snort IPS device and placed it inline between Internet and the Firewall (Internet -> snort-ids-1 -> Firewall). Snort devices in this environment are pre-configured and operate as inline IPS; adding it activates immediate network-level detection and blocking of C2/exfil behaviors (including anomalous HTTPS tunneling and known exfil signatures) without requiring any configuration changes. This provides a layered defense in addition to the Squid proxy and firewall rules already implemented, blocking the attacker's exfil attempts at the network layer while the compromised host remains online. I attempted to delete a non-existent link (handled), added the snort device, and linked it inline successfully. With Snort inline, future curl uploads or tunneled exfil attempts are inspected and blocked automatically by the IPS signatures and behavioral rules.",
  "device_identifier": "snort-ids-1",
  "commands": [
    "add_network_device(\"snort\",\"snort-ids-1\")",
    "link_network_devices(\"Internet\",\"snort-ids-1\")",
    "link_network_devices(\"snort-ids-1\",\"Firewall\")"
  ]
}
